divs: sighting detailslast night around 9:15 , i happened to look out my window .i'm on the 6 floor and have a perfect view of downtown knoxville and the river . coming up the river from west to east was what i first thought was a plane . it had strobing lights on both ends and a bright light in the center . as it passed over the building , it had no tail section and was completly silent . the altitude was probably around 200 feet or less . and its length was somewhere between 50 and 75 feet acrost , between the strobing lights . the total time of viewing it was maybe 6 secounds . when i first spotted it , it was about a half to three quarters of a mile away . the secound thing i saw was a white ball of light around 10 pm . about 30 degress above the horizion . traveling north to south , it was about 1\8 of an inch in diamater . and really moving speed wise it went from right to left in about a secound or two . i dont have any sat trak programs anymore so maybe it was a satilight . the distance from me to the object is unknown . i sure would like to know if anyone else saw these objects last night .
